  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-low heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 10-12 min or until slightly softened</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/755.step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/755.step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/755.step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/755.step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/755.step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>basmati rice</strong> and 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[390ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> <strong>cold water </strong>to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cut 3 thin slices of <strong>lemon</strong> per person</p><p>Once boiling, add your <strong>saffron</strong> and <strong>lemon slices</strong> to the rice</p><p>Reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Cut the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>lemon</strong> into wedges</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/755.step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/755.step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/755.step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/755.step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/755.step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the rice is cooking, chop your<strong> sweet potato[es]</strong> (skins on) into rough bite-sized pieces</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your<strong> garlic</strong></p><p>Once the onion has softened, add the<strong> chopped</strong> <strong>sweet potato</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and your <strong>curry powder</strong> to the pan and cook for 5 min further</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/755.step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/755.step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/755.step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/755.step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/755.step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop your <strong>creamed coconut </strong>roughly (if required!)</p><p>Dissolve the <strong>chopped creamed coconut</strong> and<strong> vegetable stock mix </strong>in 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[200ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> – this is your <strong>coconut stock</strong></p><p>Cut your <strong>tomato[es]</strong> into wedges</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-copy-3-1650388545867-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-copy-3-1650388545867-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-copy-3-1650388545867-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-copy-3-1650388545867-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-copy-3-1650388545867-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>coconut stock</strong> and <strong>tomato wedges</strong> to the pan</p><p>Increase the heat to medium-high and cook, covered, for 10 min or until the sweet potato is fork-tender</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/755.step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/755.step-5-x400.jpg",
